c t sai m hnh (Model Misspecification)

By Evgenia "Jenny" Nitishinskaya and Delaney Mackenzie

Edited by AI Cafe

M hnh ha tham s cp n vic la chn hm tng qut m chng ta ang iu chnh cho d liu. Chng ta cn chn:

  • bin ph thuc
  • bin c lp
  • dng hm

V d, chng ta c th gi nh rng bin ph thuc l mt hm tuyn tnh ca hai bin c lp. Nu m hnh khng c xc nh ng, cc gi nh hi quy s b vi phm v m hnh s khng chnh xc. Di y, chng ta s nh ngha v gii thch nhiu li ph bin trong vic xc nh m hnh.

S loi tr cc bin quan trng

Nu chng ta b qua mt bin khng c tng quan vi cc bin m chng ta a vo, n gin l chng ta s khng gii thch c bin ph thuc tt nh chng ta c th. Tuy nhin, nu bin b b qua (gi s l $X_2$) c tng quan vi bin a vo ($X_1$), th vic loi tr ny c thm mt nh hng khc. H s ca $X_1$ v hng s trong hi quy s b thin lch do c gng b p cho vic b qua $X_2$. iu ny c th khin chng ta c lng qu mc tc ng ca $X_1$ ln bin ph thuc. Ngoi ra, cc gi tr c lng ca cc h s v cc sai s chun c lng s khng nht qun.

C th, chng ta c th b dn n nim tin rng hai bin c mi quan h nhn qu do s tng quan cao ca chng, khi thc t c hai u b gy ra bi mt bin th ba. V d, nu hai c phiu u theo di th trng, hoc hai i lng u c xu hng tng theo thi gian, chng s c s tng quan cao.

start = '2023-01-01'
end = '2025-01-01'

closes = get_prices('CTG', 'VCB', 'VNINDEX', start_date=start, end_date=end).dropna()

bench = closes['VNINDEX']
a1 = closes['CTG']
a2 = closes['VCB']

# Perform linear regression and print R-squared values
slr12 = regression.linear_model.OLS(a2, sm.add_constant(a1)).fit()
slrb1 = regression.linear_model.OLS(a1, sm.add_constant(bench)).fit()
slrb2 = regression.linear_model.OLS(a2, sm.add_constant(bench)).fit()
print("R-squared values of linear regression")
print("CTG and VCB:", slr12.rsquared)
print("CTG and VNINDEX:", slrb1.rsquared)
print("VCB and VNINDEX:", slrb2.rsquared)

Tht kh thy s nht qun, hoc thiu vng n, v n l gii hn v xc sut. Tuy nhin, chng ta c th m rng khong thi gian mu ca mnh xem gi tr R-bnh phng thay i nh th no. Mi tng quan gia cc c phiu v th trng dng nh vn tn ti, trong khi mi tng quan gia hai c phiu gim. V vy, chng ta s c li hn khi d on gi c phiu t gi th trng hn l t nhau.

Cch tt nht trnh vn ny l chn cc bin c lp m bn c l do tin rng s l nhng d on tt cho bin ph thuc trc khi bt u phn tch hi quy. "Trc" l iu quan trng: vic khng chn cc bin ch da trn cch m phn tch hi quy trng nh th no l rt quan trng, v iu s dn n vic qu khp (overfitting).

S bao gm cc bin khng cn thit

Ngc li, chng ta c th c mt m hnh bao gm qu nhiu bin c lp. Nu chng ta bao gm mt bin thc s khng cn thit, chng ta s c gi tr R bnh phng iu chnh thp hn v cc c lng khng chnh xc hn cho cc h s hi quy khc. Ngha l, phn tch ca chng ta v m hnh s b suy yu, nhng chnh m hnh s khng thay i.

Tuy nhin, nu chng ta bao gm cc bin phn ln l khng lin quan, chng ta c th ci thin mt cch gi to ph hp v R-bnh phng ca m hnh bng cch thm cc bin c tng quan nh ph hp vi d liu mu. iu ny c nguy c gy ra hin tng overfitting, v nhng iu chnh nh m chng ta thc hin l c th cho mu. V d, di y chng ta thc hin mt hi quy vi gi c phiu VCB l bin c lp v gi c phiu CTG l bin ph thuc (iu ny c mt s ngha v chng cng nm trong cng mt lnh vc) v sau thc hin mt hi quy khc vi ba c phiu ngu nhin khc c thm vo.

In[13]:
start = '2024-01-01'
end = '2025-01-01'

closes = get_prices('CTG', 'VCB', 'FPT', 'VIC', 'SSI', 'VNINDEX', start_date=start, end_date=end).dropna()

x1 = closes['VCB']
x2 = closes['FPT']
x3 = closes['VIC']
x4 = closes['SSI']
y = closes['CTG']

# Build a linear model using only x1 to explain y
slr = regression.linear_model.OLS(y, sm.add_constant(x1)).fit()
slr_prediction = slr.params.iloc[0] + slr.params.iloc[1]*x1

# Run multiple linear regression using x1, x2, x3, x4 to explain y
mlr = regression.linear_model.OLS(y, sm.add_constant(np.column_stack((x1,x2,x3,x4)))).fit()
mlr_prediction = mlr.params.iloc[0] + mlr.params.iloc[1]*x1 + mlr.params.iloc[2]*x2 + mlr.params.iloc[3]*x3 + mlr.params.iloc[4]*x4

# Compute adjusted R-squared for the two different models
print('SLR R-squared:', slr.rsquared_adj)
print('MLR R-squared:', mlr.rsquared_adj)

# Plot y along with the two different predictions
y.plot()
slr_prediction.plot()
mlr_prediction.plot()
plt.legend(['CTG', 'SLR', 'MLR']);

SLR R-squared: 0.42926622665169634
MLR R-squared: 0.6713239287588028

Chng ta c th iu chnh m hnh vi nhiu bin hn mt cch chnh xc hn theo d liu. Lu rng mc d R-squared iu chnh pht chng ta v s dng nhiu bin hn, nhng s lng mu y qu ln nn s iu chnh l rt nh. Hy xem iu g xy ra nu chng ta s dng cc m hnh tuyn tnh ging nhau d on gi ca CTG trong ba thng ti:

In[14]:
start = '2025-01-01'
end = '2025-04-01'

closes = get_prices('CTG', 'VCB', 'FPT', 'VIC', 'SSI', 'VNINDEX', start_date=start, end_date=end).dropna()

x1 = closes['VCB']
x2 = closes['FPT']
x3 = closes['VIC']
x4 = closes['SSI']
y = closes['CTG']

# Extend our model from before to the new time period
slr_prediction2 = slr.params.iloc[0] + slr.params.iloc[1]*x1
mlr_prediction2 = mlr.params.iloc[0] + mlr.params.iloc[1]*x1 + mlr.params.iloc[2]*x2 + mlr.params.iloc[3]*x3 + mlr.params.iloc[4]*x4

# Compute adjusted R-squared over the extended time period
adj = float(len(y) - 1)/(len(y) - 5) # Compute adjustment factor
SST = sum((y - np.mean(y))**2)
SSRs = sum((slr_prediction2 - y)**2)
print('SLR R-squared:', 1 - adj*SSRs/SST)
SSRm = sum((mlr_prediction2 - y)**2)
print('MLR R-squared:', 1 - adj*SSRm/SST)

# Plot y along with the two different predictions
y.plot()
slr_prediction2.plot()
mlr_prediction2.plot()
plt.legend(['CTG', 'SLR', 'MLR']);

SLR R-squared: -6.041184806295779
MLR R-squared: -4.590453964826454

By gi c hai m hnh u hot ng kh km - ngha l, chng khng th duy tr hiu sut ngoi mu - nhng c bit l m hnh t hi quy tuyn tnh a bin hin ang hot ng km hn m hnh t hi quy tuyn tnh n bin. Mc d hiu sut ny c th c nhiu nguyn nhn, nhng chng ta khng nn ngc nhin v khng c l do g tin rng, v d, c phiu VIC c sc mnh gii thch thc s trong tnh hung ny.

Li trong cc bin c lp

Nu chng ta s dng ch s hoc ngy thng lm cc bin c lp, chng s khng c li. Tuy nhin, khi chng ta mun s dng gi tr ca mt c phiu $X_t$ lm bin c lp, chng ta ch c th o gi, v gi ny thng c nhiu bin ng ngu nhin nh. Do , chng ta thc s quan st $Z_t = X_t + u_t$ vi mt li $u_t$. M hnh ca chng ta l $$ Y_t = b_0 + b_1 X_t + \epsilon_t $$

tc l, mt bin no c mi quan h tuyn tnh vi gi tr ca mt c phiu. Nhng v chng ta ch bit gi tr ca $Z_t$, chng ta s s dng m hnh $$ Y_t = b_0 + b_1 Z_t + (-b_1u_t + \epsilon_t) $$

Nu $u_t$ khng c tng quan vi $X_t$, th n s c tng quan vi $Z_t$, v do , thnh phn li $-b_1u_t + \epsilon_t$ s c tng quan vi bin c lp $Z_t$. Hu qu l, cc h s s b thin lch v khng nht qun. C th, $b_1$ s b thin lch theo hng gim.

Dng hm khng chnh xc

Sau khi chng ta chn cc bin m chng ta mun a vo, chng ta cn xc nh mt hnh dng cho hm. Mc d mt hi quy yu cu hm phi tuyn tnh theo cc h s, chng ta c th thao tc cc bin t c cc loi hm khc nhau. V d, m hnh $Y_i = b_0 + b_1 X_i^2 + \epsilon_i$ cho mt mi quan h bc hai gia $X$ v $Y$, trong khi m hnh log-linear $\ln Y_i = b_0 + b_1 X_i + \epsilon_i$ cho mt mi quan h hm m. Ni chung, chng ta chn dng hm da trn k vng ca chng ta v mi quan h: v d, mt m hnh log-linear l tt khi chng ta k vng tc tng trng ca $Y$ lin quan n $X$.

Nu chn dng hm sai, chng ta c th khng t c mt s ph hp tt. Thc t, m hnh c th dn n nhng kt lun v l. V d, nu chng ta s dng mt m hnh tuyn tnh trong khi mt m hnh logarit s hp l hn, chng ta c th d on rng s lng cng ty trong mt loi nht nh tr nn m thay v gn bng khng.

Chng ta cng cn cn thn khng chn mt dng hm chc nng qu khp vi d liu. Vic s dng ty tin cc a thc bc cao dn n vic qu khp v chng c nhiu bc t do hn. Mt vn khc l khai thc d liu: nu chng ta th nhiu m hnh khc nhau cho n khi tm ra m hnh trng tt nht, chng ta ang qu khp vi mu vi ci gi l kh nng d on trong tng lai.

Tp hp cc qun th khc nhau

Nu chng ta c gng s dng mt m hnh cho hai qun th m m hnh ring bit s ph hp hn, chng ta s nhn c nhng kt qu d gy hiu lm theo mt hng no . V d, nu chng ta trn ln d liu v mc lng ca nam gii v n gii, c th s c qu nhiu s phn tn tm ra mt m hnh ph hp tt, nh trong v d gi nh di y.

In[15]:
# Generate two artificial samples and pool them
sample1 = np.arange(30) + 4*np.random.randn(30)
sample2 = sample1 + np.arange(30)
pool = np.hstack((sample1, sample2))

# Run a regression on the pooled data, with the independent variable being the original indices
model = regression.linear_model.OLS(pool, sm.add_constant(np.hstack((np.arange(30),np.arange(30))))).fit()

# Plot the two samples along with the regression line
plt.scatter(np.arange(30), sample1, color='b')
plt.scatter(np.arange(30), sample2, color='g')
plt.plot(model.params[0] + model.params[1]*np.arange(30), color='r');

R rng rng vic s dng hai m hnh ring bit cho hai tp d liu s ph hp hn. Lu rng, nh ni trn, iu ny c th dn n cc vi phm gi nh nh heteroskedasticity v cc li khng phn phi chun.

Chui thi gian khng n nh

Mt qu trnh tnh l mt qu trnh m phn phi xc sut chung ca n khng thay i theo thi gian. C th, gi tr trung bnh v phng sai ca n l hng s theo thi gian. Khi chng ta p dng cc m hnh hi quy cho chui thi gian, chng ta phi a ra gi nh b sung rng chng l n nh. Nu khng, cc thng k t ca cc tham s s khng hp l.

Mt bc i ngu nhin l mt qu trnh m c lng tt nht cho gi tr tip theo l gi tr trc ; nu bn i b ngu nhin, v tr ca bn sau mi bc s nm gn v tr ca bn trc bc nhng theo hng khng th on trc. Mt cch chnh thc, mt bc i mt chiu nh vy c m t bi phng trnh $$ x_t = x_{t-1} + \epsilon_t $$

trong sai s $\epsilon_t$ l ng phng sai, c gi tr trung bnh bng khng, v khng c t tng quan. V d, t gi hi oi thng c gi nh l cc bc i ngu nhin. Cc bc i ngu nhin c phng sai tng theo thi gian v do khng n nh. Chng d b nh hng bi cc kt qu gi mo, v hai bc i ngu nhin s xut hin c tng quan cao rt thng xuyn. Hy th chy on code di y nhiu ln:

In[16]:
# Generate normally distributed errors
randos = [np.random.randn(100) for i in range(100)]
y = np.random.randn(100)
# Generate random walks
randows = [[sum(rando[:i+1]) for i in range(100)] for rando in randos]
yw = [sum(y[:i+1]) for i in range(100)]

for i in range(100):
    plt.plot(randows[i], alpha=0.5)
In[19]:
# Compute R-squared of linear regression for each element of randows with yw
rs = [regression.linear_model.OLS(yw, x).fit().rsquared for x in randows]

# Plot and count the random walks that have R-squared with yw > .8
rcount = 0
for i in range(100):
    if rs[i] > .8:
        rcount += 1
        plt.plot(randows[i], alpha=0.5)
print('Linearly related walks out of 100:', rcount)

# Plot yw
plt.plot(yw, color='k');

Linearly related walks out of 100: 21

L do cho hai nhnh trn l v mt php hi quy tuyn tnh hot ng tt cho c cc bin c mi tng quan dng v m.

Kt qu thm ch cn cc oan hn nu chng ta xem xt cc bc i ngu nhin c mi tng quan ng k, theo gi tr p ca cc h s tng quan ca chng:

In[20]:
from scipy.stats import pearsonr

# Compute correlation coefficients (Pearson r) and record their p-values
ps = [pearsonr(yw, x)[1] for x in randows]

# Plot and count the random walks that have p-value of correlation with yw < 0.05
pcount = 0
for i in range(100):
    if ps[i] < .05:
        pcount += 1
        plt.plot(randows[i], alpha=0.5)
print('Significantly correlated walks out of 100:', pcount)

# Plot yw
plt.plot(yw, color='k');

Significantly correlated walks out of 100: 72

Bi v xc sut cao ca cc kt qu gi mo, cc thng k ph hp m chng ta tnh ton khi hi quy trn cc bc ngu nhin l khng hp l. Hn na, cc c lng tham s l khng nht qun.

Chng ta c th pht hin cc bc ngu nhin v chui thi gian lin quan (chng hn nh mt bc ngu nhin c tri) bng cch kim tra s hin din ca mt nghim n v trong chui thi gian; tc l, liu n c xut hin theo phng trnh $x_t = x_{t-1} + \epsilon_t$ hay khng. Mt phng php l s dng kim nh Dickey-Fuller:

In[21]:
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller

# Compute the p-value of the Dickey-Fuller statistic to test the null hypothesis that yw has a unit root
print(adfuller(yw)[1])

0.5108597290301998

Do , chng ta khng th bc b gi thuyt rng yw c mt nghim n v (nh chng ta bit n c, theo cu trc). Nu chng ta bit rng mt chui thi gian c mt nghim n v v chng ta vn mun phn tch n, chng ta c th m hnh ha chui sai khc u tin $y_t = x_t - x_{t-1}$ nu n l tnh, v s dng n d on cc gi tr tng lai ca $x$. Chng ta cng c th s dng hi quy nu c bin ph thuc v bin c lp u l cc chui thi gian c nghim n v v hai bin ny c ng lin kt.
